<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><title>Meer as ooit en Above all</title>
<time_sig>Style: 024 en Tempo 69</time_sig>
<key>G</key>
<lyrics>[V1]
.G        C     D         G
 Meer as rykdom, meer as mag,
.         C                   D         G
 as die skoonheid van sterre in die nag,
.G       Em                    C/G
 meer as wat ons ooit op aarde wen,
.Am                            D
 is dit werd, o Heer, om U te ken.

[V2]
.          C    D         G
 Meer as silwer, meer as geld,
.        C            D           G
 Al die blomme, die diere in die veld,
.        Em                      C/G
 Meer as dit, so eindeloos veel meer,
.Am                              B
 Was die prys wat U betaal het, Heer.

[C1]
.  G      Am       D                G
   Aan 'n kruis en in 'n graf van steen,
.  G          Am        D         G
   U leef en sterf, verworpe en alleen.
.  G    Em                C/G
   Immanuel, U die God met ons
.  G          Am               C  (D)
   U dra die straf en dink aan ons
.           G
   Meer as ooit

[V3]
. G         C     D           G
 Above all powers, above all kings,
.G         C          D           G
 Above all nature and all created things.
.          Em                         C  G
 Above all wisdom and all the ways of man,
.Am            Am                D
 You were here before the world began.

[V4]
.           C       D            G
 Above all kingdoms, above all thrones.
.          C            D              G
 Above all wonders this world has ever known.
.          Em                          C  G
 Above all wealth and treasures of the earth,
.Am                Am                   B
 There's no way to measure what you're worth.

[C2]
.  G    Am    D               G
   Crucified, laid behind the stone,
.      G         Am      D          G
   You lived and died, rejected and alone.
.         Em                    C    G
   Like a rose, trampled on the ground
.               Am                   C  D      G
   You took the fall, and thought of me, above all.

[B1]
.         Em                    C    G
   Like a rose, trampled on the ground
.               Am                   C  D      G
   You took the fall, and thought of me, above all.</lyrics>
</song>